PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1782551897
OL,3,CAndy Burnham to set out economic
OL,4,Cvision in first major speech of
OL,5,Cleadership bid
OL,7,FRachel Reeves appears to have conceded
OL,8,Fshe will no longer be staying on as
OL,9,FChancellor, with several senior
OL,10,Fministers including Home Secretary
OL,11,FShabana Mahmood and Energy Secretary
OL,12,FEd Miliband reportedly in the running
OL,13,Fto succeed her.
OL,15,FAn unlikely alliance of some trade
OL,16,Funionists and city traders have
OL,17,Freportedly urged Mr Burnham against
OL,18,Fappointing Mr Miliband as chancellor,
OL,19,Fbecause they believe his net zero
OL,20,Fpolicies to be damaging.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1782551897
OL,3,CAndy Burnham to set out economic
OL,4,Cvision in first major speech of
OL,5,Cleadership bid
OL,7,FBut transport union the TSSA has
OL,8,Fthrown its weight behind Mr Miliband.
OL,10,FQuestions also remain over whether Ms
OL,11,FMahmood will remain at the Home
OL,12,FOffice, with some Labour figures
OL,13,Fsaying he should scrap her proposals
OL,14,Fto increase the length of time
OL,15,Fimmigrants have to wait to apply for
OL,16,Findefinite leave to remain in the UK.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/6
